Sentencas: Ce0.8Sm0.1Nd0.1O2-delta (SNDC) is one of the most promising electrolyte materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Elevated sintering capability and electrical conductivity of Fe2O3-doped Ce0.8Sm0.1Nd0.1O2-δ as an electrolyte in IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: However, the adverse effect on the preparation of the electrolyte due to the high sintering temperature of SNDC limits the application of SNDC as an electrolyte material in IT-SOFCs.
Titulo: Elevated sintering capability and electrical conductivity of Fe2O3-doped Ce0.8Sm0.1Nd0.1O2-δ as an electrolyte in IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: In this work, x mol % (x = 0, 0.5, 1.0, 1.5, 2.0, 2.5) Fe-doped SNDC (xFe-SNDC) powders were firstly fabricated by sol-gel synthesis, and then the corresponding bulks were prepared by cold-pressing and sintering at 1200 similar to 1400 degrees C.
Titulo: Elevated sintering capability and electrical conductivity of Fe2O3-doped Ce0.8Sm0.1Nd0.1O2-δ as an electrolyte in IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: The effects of Fe-doping on the sintering capability and electrical conductivity of SNDC were investigated.
Titulo: Elevated sintering capability and electrical conductivity of Fe2O3-doped Ce0.8Sm0.1Nd0.1O2-δ as an electrolyte in IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: The results showed that Fe-doping leads to significant improvements in both the relative density and the electrical conductivity of SNDC.
Titulo: Elevated sintering capability and electrical conductivity of Fe2O3-doped Ce0.8Sm0.1Nd0.1O2-δ as an electrolyte in IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: Doping Fe reduced the sintering temperature of SNDC from 1400 degrees C to 1200 degrees C and the relative density of 0.5Fe-SNDC sintered at 1200 degrees C reached 95.85%.
Titulo: Elevated sintering capability and electrical conductivity of Fe2O3-doped Ce0.8Sm0.1Nd0.1O2-δ as an electrolyte in IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: Moreover, 0.5Fe-SNDC possessed the maximum conductivity of 0.0674 S cm(-1) at 750 degrees C, which was attributed to the highest density and the highest conductivity of grain plus grain boundary.
Titulo: Elevated sintering capability and electrical conductivity of Fe2O3-doped Ce0.8Sm0.1Nd0.1O2-δ as an electrolyte in IT-SOFCs
